---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<main class="px-8 py-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto font-mono text-neutral-100 bg-neutral-950 leading-relaxed">
  <h1 class="text-3xl mb-6">The Groundative Tradition</h1>

  <p>
    The Groundative Tradition stands upon a single law: <strong>What is, is.</strong>
    From this, all knowledge, art, and ethics return to their source — Reality itself.
  </p>

  <p>
    It is not a belief, theory, or movement of opinion. It is a descriptive-presential
    system that reveals what is already the case. Presence before proposition.
    Fact before theory. Being before belief.
  </p>

  <p>
    Founded by XYNACT, the Tradition establishes a science of reality itself:
    a discipline of standing in the real, perceiving without mediation,
    and acting with integrity. It joins philosophy, art, and civic life into
    one continuum of knowing-being.
  </p>

  <p>
    The first canonical work, <em>The Groundative Treatise · Volume I — Foundation</em>,
    defines the framework, laws, and methods of this return to ground.
    Each volume to come extends its praxis into art, education, and society.
  </p>

  <p>
    To enter the Tradition is not to adopt belief, but to stand where the world
    begins again — in the unabstracted real.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-10">
    <a href="/works" class="px-5 py-2 border border-neutral-700 text-neutral-100 hover:bg-neutral-800 transition">
      Read the Treatise
    </a>
  </div>
</main>
